## The Golden Rule рҹ”‘

| Region | xвҲ’1 sign | xвҲ’5 sign |
|--------|----------|----------|
| x < 1 | вҲ’ | вҲ’ |
| 1вүӨx<5 | + | вҲ’ |
| x вүҘ 5 | + | + |

The sign **flips** every time you cross a critical point!

Excellent question! This is a very common confusion. Let me explain clearly.

---

## For a SINGLE absolute value
```
|x - 3| = 5
```
Yes, only **2 cases:**
```
вҶҗвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖўвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҶ’
        x=3

Case 1: x < 3  вҶ’ -(x-3)
Case 2: x вүҘ 3  вҶ’ (x-3)
```
Simple! Just 2 regions.

---

## But when you have TWO absolute values
```
|x-1| and |x-5|
```
Each one has **its own critical point**, so together they create **3 regions:**

```
вҶҗвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖўвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖўвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҶ’
        x=1          x=5
```

Think of it like **2 fences** dividing a field into **3 sections:**

```
  SECTION 1  | SECTION 2  | SECTION 3
   x < 1     | 1 вүӨ x < 5  |  x вүҘ 5
             |            |
          fence 1      fence 2
```

---

## The Simple Rule рҹ”‘

> **Number of cases = Number of critical points + 1**

| Critical Points | Cases |
|----------------|-------|
| 1 point | 2 cases |
| 2 points | 3 cases |
| 3 points | 4 cases |

---

## Why do we need all 3 regions?

Because the **signs change** at each critical point:

```
вҶҗвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖўвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖўвҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҖ”вҶ’
        x=1          x=5

SECTION 1    SECTION 2    SECTION 3
(x-1) = вҲ’    (x-1) = +    (x-1) = +
(x-5) = вҲ’    (x-5) = вҲ’    (x-5) = +
```

See how between x=1 and x=5, the **two expressions have DIFFERENT signs?**

That middle region behaves differently from both sides, so it **must** be its own case!

---

